<div id="review_3212836140" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3212836140" />
    <a title="John Hatley" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4161383-john-hatley"><img alt="John Hatley" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1538046605p2/4161383.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3212836140?book_show_action=true">Mar 01, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="John Hatley" class="user" itemprop="url" name="John Hatley" href="/user/show/4161383-john-hatley">John Hatley</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 0460113070" href="/book/show/7014404-canterbury-tales">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3212836140" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10216302368731772657">This is one of those books I read as a student of language. It is also one of the most significant works in the English language. The <i>Canterbury Tales</i> give students of the English language an excellent sample of Middle English (200 years <b>before</b> Shakespeare). At the same time, they provide an unparalleled glimpse of life in fourteenth-century England. To the adventurous I recommend reading it in the original Middle English.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


